    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for Model Risk Level 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2. The CFD model demonstrates sufficient credibility to support the regulatory claim that worst-case hemolysis operating conditions have been identified for the Class II CPB device. The 95th-percentile RH prediction of 0.94 satisfies the RH < 1 acceptance criterion with adequate margin. Uncertainty quantification confirms that input variability does not challenge the acceptance criterion under the propagated uncertainty bounds.",
